    <li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Then the chlorinated water is pumped to sand filter evenly  distributed through the send media and filtered. The suspended matter in water is  removed and filtered.</li>
<li >&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;From send filter the water passes to Activated carbon filter which removes the chlorine and impurities  present in water. it also removes bad smell if present in water.</li>
<li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Then it passes through the micron filter of 10 & 5 micron, which  removes the micro  suspended particles  in water After which antiscedant is dosed.</li>
<li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Then the water passes to the R.O  System. The system consists of panel board and skid to mount the high pressure pump, RO Housing and membrane. Ro is a process used to removed dissolved salts  (98% -99%)from water.</li>

